                    <p>Here it is. This is the BBJ Hall of Fame. The following players have proven their infinite wisdom and superiority over the years in the BBJ, and they have earned themselves a place of their own in its history. They are gods among men and kings among the sport of the sport. These Hall of Fame players are the epitome of the game.</p>
                    <p class="bold">To be eligible for the BBJ Hall of Fame, a player must earn two wins and another top-three finish.</p>

                    <div id="bbj">
                        <h2 class="border">Basket Ball Jones (1976)</h2>
                        <h3>5 wins</h3>
                        <p>(1972, 1974, 1978, 1990, 2001)</p>
                        <h3>38 years played</h3>
                        <p>(1971-2008)</p>
                        <p>The creator of the world-famous BBJ NCAA Pick-off earned the first induction into the Hall of Fame by proving his greatness and supremacy in the early years of the Pick-off. He earned his first win in the second annual Pick-off in 1972. He was victorious two years later in 1974. He sealed his spot early in the Hall of Fame with a runner-up finish in 1976, the sixth Pick-off. He played every single year available in his lifetime, and was a dominant player until the end. His achievements include 5 wins and 7 runner-up finishes, a feat that will stay around for a very long time if not forever. His last appearance in the top 3 was with a win in 2001. Basket Ball Jones is the greatest of all time.</p>
                        <p>Nobody really knows exactly who Basket Ball Jones was. BBJ is, of course, an alias, and his true identity is known only to a select few players whom help him adminsitrate the pick-off. One thing is for sure though, and that was his great annual performance. You could always look for him near the top of the leaderboard. In 2005, he passed down duties as Gamesmaster for the Pick-off to his heir, Basket Ball Jones Jr. Only time will tell if his capable heir will follow in the big footsteps of the King of Kings, Basket Ball Jones.</p>
                    </div><!-- end #bbj -->
