                    <div id="kdmoir">
                        <h2 class="border">K d. Moir (1987)</h2>
                        <h3>3 wins</h3>
                        <p>(1976, 1981, 1987)</p>
                        <h3>38 years played</h3>
                        <p>(1971-2008)</p>
                        <p>The only other player to participate every year besides the creator and infamous Basket Ball Jones was K. d. Moir. He was a constant in the BBJ. K. d. Moir passed away in January 2009, but memories of him will last forever. His impact on the BBJ Pick-off itself and the core players is beyond substantial. He was notorious for his annual support of the Indiana Hoosiers in the Pick-off, and he displayed his fanaticalness by picking his Hoosiers to win it all every single year. He also tended to favor Big Ten teams through the tournament. Because his beloved Hoosiers won the NCAA championship in 1976, 1981, and 1987, his entries did very well. In fact, those are the three years he won the BBJ Pick-off. His entries were no joke, however, because his team was also favored by others in those years and especially so in 1976. Some called Kdmoir a clown, but no clown can win the BBJ three times.</p>
                        <p>K. d. Moir was known also for his not-so-quiet and not-unpopular opinion of Myles Brand & Mike "Lame" Davis and his appreciation of Coach Knight. When Mike Davis failed to lead IU to the NCAA tournament in 2004 and 2005, Kdmoir swiched his allegiance to Coach Knight's new team, Texas Tech, which was in the tournament.</p>
                        <p>K. d. Moir had an invaluable role in the BBJ Pick-off as a recruiter, and his contributions have been vital to the growth of the BBJ NCAA Pick-off.</p>
                    </div><!-- end #kdmoir -->
