                    <div id="accblows">
                        <h2 class="border">ACC Blows (1992)</h2>
                        <h3>2 wins</h3>
                        <p>(1988, 1992)</p>
                        <h3>?? years played</h3>
                        <p>(varied from early '80s to mid '90s)</p>
                        <p>ACC Blows is one of the most creative names among the players in the BBJ. This player is a mystery because nobody knows his true identity. The last appearance of ACC Blows is unknown, but the alias has not been used for many years. It is estimated that it was abandoned in the Pick-off in the mid-90s, a few years after the last win. However, it is suspected that the player has used other names in the BBJ. ACC Blows fulfilled his first requirement for Hall of Fame induction in 1982, early in his BBJ career, with a runner-up finish. He achieved his two wins in 1988 and 1992. His participation in the Pick-off has not been consistent, but the name will live forever as one of the very few players to achieve admired greatness and induction into the BBJ Hall of Fame.</p>
                    </div><!-- end #accblows -->
