                    <div id="ajmoir">
                        <h2 class="border">A.J. Moir (2000)</h2>
                        <h3>3 wins</h3>
                        <p>(1999, 2000, 2009)</p>
                        <h3>14 years played</h3>
                        <p>(1996-2000, 2004-present)</p>
                        <p>A.J. Moir is the youngest player ever to win the BBJ NCAA Pick-off and the youngest to be inducted into the BBJ Hall of Fame. He began playing in 1996 at age 8 and earned a third-place finish. He continued from there and was runner-up in 1998. He won his first BBJ Pick-off in 1999, his fourth attempt. He followed up that win with another in 2000 to become eligible for the Hall of Fame at the young age of 12. It is said that he unfortunately abandoned the Pick-off from from 2001-2003 because of IU's coaching situation, however, he did return in 2004 and was runner-up to the sure-to-be future Hall of Fame player, Basket Ball Jones Jr. In 2005, he was one point shy of third place. He placed in 5 of his first 6 attempts, a feat that is doubtful to be doubled. This player has definitely proven his greatness early in his BBJ career, and he poses a major threat to all players every year.</p>
                        <p>His most recent achievement is a third win in 2009. Regardless of where he places, he is a valuable part of the BBJ through his recruiting.</p>
                    </div><!-- end #ajmoir -->
